devdoc.title: Distributor contract - distribution of tokens after an auction has ended.
Distributor contract - distribution of tokens after an auction has ended.

devdoc.author: [..] credits to Stefan George - <stefan.george@consensys.net>

bid().details: Allows to send a bid to the auction.

bid(address).details: Allows to send a bid to the auction.

changeSettings(uint256,uint256).details: Changes auction start price factor before auction is started.

claimTokens().details: Claims tokens for bidder after auction. To be used if tokens can be claimed by bidders, individually.

claimTokens(address).details: Claims tokens for bidder after auction.

params.receiver: Tokens will be assigned to this address if set.

missingReserveToEndAuction().details: The missing reserve amount necessary to end the auction at the current price.

missingReserveToEndAuction(uint256).details: The missing reserve amount necessary to end the auction at the current price, for a provided reserve/balance.

params.reserve: Reserve amount - might be current balance or current balance without current bid value for bid().

price().return: Returns num Wei per TKN (multiplier * Tei).

setup(address).details: Setup function sets external contracts' addresses.

params.terms_address_hash: valid param is sha3(terms_hash, msg.sender) to enforce individual agreement

devdoc.title: Dutch auction contract - distribution of tokens using an auction.

allowance(address,address).details: Returns number of allowed tokens for given address.

approve(address,uint256).details: Sets approved amount of tokens for spender. Returns success.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns number of tokens owned by given address.

burn(uint256).details: Allows to destroy tokens without receiving the corresponding amount of ether

receiveReserve().details: Transfers auction's reserve; called from auction after it has ended.

redeem(uint256).details: Allows to destroy tokens and receive the corresponding amount of ether, implements the floor price

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfers sender's tokens to a given address. Returns success.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Allows allowed third party to transfer tokens from one address to another. Returns success.

params._from: Address from where tokens are withdrawn.
params._to: Address to where tokens are sent.
